Kubernates k8s(this is the short form for kubernates after k there are 8 letters and then s hence k8s)
Expect all image to already be built
One config file per object we want to create
We have to manually setup all n/w-king

We have to create config files for an object and that object will further used
apiversion and kind in yaml
there we have stndrd api version and according to that we have kind
examples:
api version v1
kind pod

api version api v1
kind service under service we have nodeport for dev only not use for production, clusterapi, ingress

Pod: consist of container which help to acheive an independent that and they are tightly coupled
Eg: dd agent and service

The Concept: How a Service knows which Pods to route traffic to. You "Label" a Pod (e.g., component: web) and the Service uses a "Selector" to find it.

Interview Tip: Think of Labels as the "glue" that connects different K8s objects together without hard-coding IP addresses.

